org.remoteHome

Class TemperatureSensorDevice

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.remoteHome.AbstractDevice
      • org.remoteHome.TemperatureSensorDevice
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AbstractDevice>

    public class TemperatureSensorDevice
extends AbstractDevice
implements java.io.Serializable
    Temperature sensor
    pn - check weather the device is up and running (ping command).
    m=nnn - set the frequency and put to the sleep mode. 1 means 10 seconds, 255 means 2550 seconds. Needs to be set to put the device to sleep mode!!!
          If not set, or set to 0, then no sleep - usefull for testing, but consume lot of power and batery will be quicly empty.
    s - return status 2|temperature|battery|frequency
          temperature format - always sign, 2 decimals degree celsius, dot, 2 decimals, e.g +23.32 or -02.32 or +02.20
          battery voltage e.g. 2.9 or 3.0
          frequency - frequency in seconds to send status. Longer value, longer battery life

    Quick startup:

    1. Insert the battery
    2. Test the communication AT+0=pn
    3. Assign the device ID: AT+a=5 Id is 5.
    4. Test the device: AT+5=s Should return back the status.
    5. Configure the sleep period: AT+5=m=60 This means 10 minutes timeout (60 * 10) seconds = 600 / 60 = 10 mins.
    6. Now you can use this API.

      • manageAsynchronousCommand

        protected void manageAsynchronousCommand(java.lang.String[] items)
        Description copied from class: AbstractDevice
        This method is called by the Remote home manager. If you register your device to receive the asynchronous events, the communication class will call this method to set the values of the specific device type. Please note, that this method is called in the same thread as the receiving thread, so the implementation should be fast enough to return as soon as possible.
        Specified by:
        manageAsynchronousCommand in class AbstractDevice
        Parameters:
        items - the data from asynchronous event. Could be: 2|temperature|battery|frequency - status
